The builds occur once a day.  Depending on when you push it can take up to 48 hours to see the results on the build report page.  See
https://contributions.bioconductor.org/troubleshooting-build-report.html
which has some suggest times.

Likely, you pushed too late on Monday October 10th to see the change in yesterday's (Tue) build report.  I would expect to see the changes on today's.  The changes you pushed up today (an additional version bump) would not appear until tomorrow or Friday.

The landing page for the package will not be updated until the build report has propagated results.  Normally a few hours after the daily report is posted.

