From: Lor|@Shepherd @end|ng |rom Ro@we||P@rk@org (Kern, Lori)
Date: Fri, 21 Oct 2022 18:12:05 +0000
Subject: [Bioc-devel] List of Deprecated Packages for Bioc3.16
Message-ID: <BL1PR12MB5301AFD47CE09D6288D7CED4F92D9@BL1PR12MB5301.namprd12.prod.outlook.com>

The Bioconductor Team is continuing to identify packages that will be deprecated in the next release to allow for the Bioconductor community to respond accordingly. This is the current list of deprecated packages for Bioc 3.16:


Software:


User Requested:

  *   AffyCompatible
  *   BitSeq
  *   flowUtils
  *   flowCL
  *   PoTRA
  *   TCGAbiolinksGUI
  *   TDARACNE
  *   tspair

Unresponsive:

  *   BrainSABER
  *   bridge
  *   cellTree
  *   ctgGEM
  *   coexnet
  *   coMET
  *   conclus
  *   CytoTree
  *   DEComplexDisease
  *   gaia
  *   gpart
  *   inveRsion
  *   IsoGeneGUI
  *   iteremoval
  *   MACPET
  *   Rcade
  *   RNASeqR
  *   scAlign
  *   scMAGeCK
  *   sojourner
  *   TimeSeriesExperiment
  *   TraRe
  *   XCIR

ExperimentData


User Requested:

  *   gatingMLData

Unresponsive:

  *   RNASeqRData

It should be noted, we did try to reach out to these package maintainers multiple times and they were either unresponsive or had emails bounce. We encourage anyone that is familiar with a package maintainer on this list to reach out to them and notify them directly. Packages can be un-deprecated if a maintainer fixes the package to build/check cleanly before the next release and requests un-deprecation on the bioc-devel at r-project.org mailing list

Please do not un-deprecate packages on your own. You need to notify the Bioconductor Core Team to do this.





